Mary Frances HENRY, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. GENERAL MOTORS CORPORATION, Defendant-Appellee. No. 229, Docket 29159. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit.

Argued Dec. 11, 1964.

Decided Dec. 11, 1964. John F. Henry, Mattydale, N. Y., for •plaintiff-appellant. Costello, Cooney & Fearon, Syracuse, N. Y. (Charles E. Cooney, Jr., Syracuse, TST. Y., Edward J. McGratty, Jr., Detroit, Mich.), for defendant-appellee.

Before WATERMAN, MOORE and jKAUFMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order below dismissing the complaint of plaintiff-appellant is affirmed on the opinion below of Judge Brennan, D.C., 236 F.Supp. 854.
